    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-28T15:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-28T15:36:00-05:00" n="175"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24400: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-28T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>348. Press confirms reported rebellion of Governor Cantu in northern district
                    Lower California and states that measures are being taken to suffocate this new
                    movement against the Government.</p>
                <p>It is reported that 2,700 troops under the command of General Abelardo Rodríguez
                    left here July 25th <hi rend="italic">en route</hi> to Ensenada by sea from
                    Manzanillo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
